>Vehicle: 1978 Westy
Question: After spending some more time this weekend rewiring/reconnecting
the dash I came up with a question... Does anyone have a list of the fuses
and their sizes? There are 12 fuses in <

fuse 1 - Side marker Light left rear, Tail Light Left  looks like a 8 amp

Fuse 2 - License Plate light, Parking lights, Side marker lights front, Side
marker light right rear, Tail light right - looks like an 8

Fuse 3 - Low beam left  8 amp

Fuse 4 - Low beam right - 8 amp

Fuse 5 - High beam left and high beam indicator light - 8 amp

Fuse 6 - High Beam right - 8 amp

Fuse 7 - Unassigned  - 8 amp

Fuse 8 - Emergency flasher system, interior light front, interior light
rear - 8 amp

Fuse 9 - Auxillary Heater )switch current), Buzzer alarm - 16 amp

Fuse 10 - Auxillary Heater(switch current), Rear window defogger(switch
current), Windshield wipers - 8 amp

Fuse 11 - Backup lights(automatic Tranny only), Fuel gauge, Kickdown(auto
tranny), Turn signals, Generator Warning light, Oil pressure warnig light -
16 amp

Fuse 12 - Horn, Stop lights, brake warning light - 8 amp


hope this helps

